comments.text:
Hi. Do you know why certain comments get unduly deleted. I had posted few of my thoughts and questions, and it was not offensive at all. But it got deleted. And the thing is when you write a long post and you don't copy it. It becomes a huge burden to find that train of thought and type in again. It's very discouraging. 

Especially when replying to people. Certain lies or probably people with innocent ignorance can comment something blatantly untrue in one or two lines, but to explain it with a bit of nuance takes a few more. And it's extremely disappointing when the effort disappears. 

Also, this is how, I feel social media including YouTube is discouraging nuance and subtlety and pushing the formation of echo chambers. Because you can't sit and reason out everything and when honest commentators do it, they get deleted, so they'll stop doing it altogether, and the voice of reason just starts to get quieter.
